“Border Patrol sources "tell me that this situation is 'out-of-control.' They need help. They say there aren't even enough porta-potties or food or anything...It looks like a large refugee camp." ~ @bmelugin33 ~ @foxnews

node.text:
Several top officials from the ousted Western-backed government have gathered in the Panjshir Valley. They include Vice President Amrullah Saleh, who claims to be the caretaker leader after President Ashraf Ghani fled the country.

They have vowed to resist the Taliban and are calling for Western aid to help roll them back.

Most people don’t know that the VP of Afghanistan did not flee the country, but instead fled into the Panjshir Valley. 

“I watched this.  This man wants strength from the US.  Biden has shown the entire world he is WEAK.  My fears are we will have another 9/11 or worse. Biden lied saying the the Afghan soldiers gave up.  I am sick of Lyin Biden. When will people and those that are to represent us stand up, grow a set, and get down to business.  We have got to get OUR people out of Afghanistan and those that helped our troops. Joe Biden, Kamela Harris, Nancy Pelosi need to be removed from their respective offices and held for Treason.  Over 85 BILLION dollars of weapons were handed over to the enemy.  Not to mention the names of those who helped us. “

node.title: VP of Afghanistan wants strength from the U.S. but gets WEAKNESS

Pentagon officials just admitted a ‘tragic’ mistake; killing 10 civilians (7 of which were children) in a drone strike in Afghanistan.

And the Border Patrol is overwhelmed with nearly 12,000 illegals in Del Rio, Texas - Mayor of Del Rio calls for Joe Biden to send help, but those calls go unanswered. 

Where is Joe Biden? He departed for his vacation with no comment and no action. 

Where is QueMala Harris? Nobody knows.

This Administration is a disaster

Thank you France 🇫🇷 for doing what Joe Biden could never do.. Thank you 🙏 

A notorious ISIS leader with a $5million dollar price tag on his head for killing 4 American special forces soldiers has been assassinated by the French military. 

The French military reportedly killed ISIS leader Adnan Abou Walid al Sahraoui, who claimed responsibility for masterminding the ambush-style murder of four U.S. special forces soldiers during a 2017 attack .

Those killed in the 2017 attack included Army Sgt. David Johnson and Staff Sgts. Bryan Black, Jeremiah Johnson, and Dustin Wright. Four Nigerian troops were also killed in the attack, and at least two American soldiers and eight Nigerian soldiers were severely wounded as a result of the siege.

node.text:
Caravans forming heading to United States. A total of 4 caravans converged this past week. These Caravan left Tapachula, Mexico destined to reach the United States. The Mexican national guard were able to dismantle some of the caravan, but those who got through are now using other routes avoiding the main routes of travel attempting to avoid the Mexican National Guard.

Another massive migrant caravan that was scheduled to leave on September 15 from Tapachula, Mexico was delayed, but will leave soon informed the activist Luis García Villagrán.

The human rights defender pointed out that the guidelines are still being adjusted to be able to leave in a massive group from this border city to the center of the country.

"The shelters are being prepared so that the migrants are not detained, so that takes time but they will leave in a caravan," he said.
